    GOSH launches as the first ever Git blockchainGOSH 作为第一个 Git 区块链发布

    May 10, 20222022 年 5 月 10 日
    Developers will be able to transparently track and verify all the code they build while ensuring malicious code will be noticeable immediately.开发人员将能够透明地跟踪和验证他们构建的所有代码，同时确保立即注意到恶意代码。

    May 10th, 2022 – Announced at DockerCon, GOSH launched as the first blockchain in history custom-built for git on-chain. GOSH has partnered with Docker to secure the software supply chain with the GOSH Docker extension. GOSH’s mission is to offer a comprehensive solution to securing the global software supply chain, which has long been a big problem for businesses, and capturing the value locked in open source projects.2022 年 5 月 10 日——在 DockerCon 上宣布，GOSH 作为历史上第一个为 git on-chain 定制构建的区块链推出。 GOSH 与 Docker 合作，通过 GOSH Docker 扩展来保护软件供应链。 GOSH 的使命是提供一个全面的解决方案来保护全球软件供应链，这长期以来一直是企业面临的一个大问题，并获取开源项目中锁定的价值。

    “Storing git on-chain is a no-brainer,” said Mitja Goroshevsky, CTO of EverX and GOSH co-founder, “attacks happen daily, and blockchain is the only technology which is widely used and is incredibly secure. The only problem: it was impossible to store git on-chain, until now. But GOSH isn’t just about security, it’s about offering developers a better git overall.EverX 首席技术官兼 GOSH 联合创始人 Mitja Goroshevsky 说：“将 git 存储在链上是一件很容易的事，攻击每天都在发生，而区块链是唯一一种被广泛使用且非常安全的技术。唯一的问题是：直到现在，都不可能将 git 存储在链上。但 GOSH 不仅仅是关于安全性，它是关于为开发人员提供更好的整体 git。

    “Git management systems available today, apart from not being secure, are also not tailored to open source. The management of the software always involves handing over code to a centralized party, and there has so far been no community management of code. GOSH changes this by allowing developers to turn their git repositories into a DAO and build consensus around your code.”“今天可用的 Git 管理系统，除了不安全之外，也不适合开源。软件的管理总是涉及将代码交给中心化的一方，目前还没有代码的社区管理。 GOSH 通过允许开发人员将他们的 git 存储库转变为 DAO 并围绕您的代码建立共识来改变这一点。”

    The current software supply chain is vulnerable to security and transparency risks, and containers are particularly susceptible. Because of this, the team behind GOSH is delighted to announce their first partnership. The GOSH Docker extension is a tool to verify that Docker containers built from GOSH remain secure and unchanged. Developers can be sure that the container itself was built only using the components they indicated in their smart contracts.当前的软件供应链容易受到安全和透明度风险的影响，容器尤其容易受到影响。因此，GOSH 背后的团队很高兴地宣布他们的第一个合作伙伴关系。 GOSH Docker 扩展是一个工具，用于验证从 GOSH 构建的 Docker 容器是否保持安全和不变。开发人员可以确定容器本身是仅使用他们在智能合约中指定的组件构建的。

    Using GOSH requires no workflow adjustments from developers, and is still very much a git. Only now, developers will be able to transparently track and verify all the code they build, instead of just relying on social metrics, such as stars and ratings. Code can be tracked to distribution, and all the elements of software are traceable back to the source code, also ensuring malicious code will be noticeable immediately.使用 GOSH 不需要开发人员调整工作流程，并且仍然是一个 git。只有现在，开发人员才能透明地跟踪和验证他们构建的所有代码，而不是仅仅依赖于社交指标，例如星级和评级。代码可以追踪到分发，软件的所有元素都可以追溯到源代码，也确保了恶意代码会立即被发现。

    GOSH is already actively working with Amaze and BitRezus on making sure their supply chains are air tight. “Here at Amaze we have become passionate about NFTs. A cornerstone of a new and exciting technology that promises to create great value to our customers, from creators to entrepreneurs, we now offer them the opportunity to mint and create minted templates for NFTs,” said Aaron Day, CEO of Amaze, “The nature of the services we provide means safety is top priority. We need to make sure that when users deal with financial tools their funds aren’t in any danger. GOSH technology can guarantee that our code is developed and delivered in a secure way so software is never compromised.”GOSH 已经在积极与 Amaze 和 BitRezus 合作，以确保他们的供应链是气密的。 “在 Amaze，我们对 NFT 充满热情。作为一项令人兴奋的新技术的基石，它有望为我们的客户（从创造者到企业家）创造巨大价值，我们现在为他们提供了为 NFT 铸造和创造铸造模板的机会，”Amaze 首席执行官 Aaron Day 说，“大自然我们提供的服务意味着安全是重中之重。我们需要确保用户在使用金融工具时，他们的资金没有任何风险。 GOSH 技术可以保证我们的代码以安全的方式开发和交付，因此软件永远不会受到损害。”

    BitRezus CEO Konstantinos Antonakopoulos added: “Astropledge works to prevent cybercrime and securely provide software to satellites using the best technology for the task: the blockchain. Our aim is to protect assets sent to space from the dangers posed from hackers or human error. Adopting GOSH is a natural evolutionary step for us, seeing as it is the only blockchain that secures the services we provide in delivering software to a satellite, securely.”BitRezus 首席执行官 Konstantinos Antonakopoulos 补充说：“Astropledge 致力于防止网络犯罪，并使用最适合任务的技术：区块链，安全地向卫星提供软件。我们的目标是保护发送到太空的资产免受黑客或人为错误造成的危险。采用 GOSH 对我们来说是自然而然的进化步骤，因为它是唯一能够保护我们在向卫星安全地交付软件时提供的服务的区块链。”

    About GOSH关于GOSH

    GOSH stands for Git Open Source Hodler. It is a decentralized community Git blockchain, purpose-built for securing the software supply chain. GOSH is the first and only formally verified Git implementation. Built as an advanced scalable multithreaded and multi-sharded blockchain, it allows developers to build a layer of structural security smart contracts therefore making it the first platform where the more code you write the more secure it becomes. It was founded on May 10th, 2022.GOSH 代表 Git Open Source Hodler。它是一个分散的社区 Git 区块链，专为保护软件供应链而构建。 GOSH 是第一个也是唯一一个正式验证的 Git 实现。作为先进的可扩展多线程和多分片区块链构建，它允许开发人员构建结构安全智能合约层，因此使其成为第一个平台，您编写的代码越多，它就越安全。它成立于2022年5月10日。
